## Scenario 002 - Privileged Command Usage & Account Administration

### Objective

Generate privileged Linux activity through `sudo` in order to validate Splunk log collection, dashboard visibility, and privileged activity monitoring.

This scenario is distinct from privilege escalation. The goal is to observe administrative actions performed by an already authorized user.

---

### Environment

| Host     | IP        | Role         |
| -------- | --------- | ------------ |
| Debian13 | 10.10.4.1 | Attacker     |
| Ubuntu24 | 10.10.6.3 | Linux Target |
| Splunk   | 10.10.5.X | SIEM         |

---

### Initial Access

A valid SSH session was established on Ubuntu24 using the account:

```text
karen
```

The account already possessed sudo privileges.

---

### Administrative Activity

Several privileged commands were executed to generate audit events:

```bash
sudo whoami
sudo id
sudo cat /etc/passwd
sudo cat /etc/shadow
```

These actions generated authentication and sudo execution events in:

```text
/var/log/auth.log
```

which were forwarded to Splunk through the Universal Forwarder.

---

### Account Administration Activity

To generate additional privileged activity, multiple local accounts inspired by Elden Ring characters were created:

```text
margit
godrick
rennala
radahn
rykard
morgott
mohg
malenia
maliketh
godfrey
```

Example commands:

```bash
sudo adduser margit
sudo adduser godrick
...
```

The accounts were then granted sudo permissions:

```bash
sudo usermod -aG sudo margit
sudo usermod -aG sudo godrick
...
```

---

### Splunk Detection

Relevant dashboard panel:

```text
Top Privileged Activities
```

Example SPL:

```spl
index=linux host=vUbu24 sourcetype=linux_auth "COMMAND="
| rex "COMMAND=(?<command>.*)"
| eval action=case(
    match(command,"adduser"),"User Creation",
    match(command,"usermod"),"Privilege Modification",
    match(command,"passwd"),"Password Change",
    match(command,"cat /etc/shadow"),"Shadow File Access",
    match(command,"cat /etc/passwd"),"Passwd File Access",
    match(command,"whoami"),"Identity Check",
    match(command,"id"),"Privilege Enumeration",
    true(),"Other")
| stats count by action
| sort -count
```

---

### Expected Detection Coverage

| Activity                      | Detection |
| ----------------------------- | --------- |
| sudo usage                    | Yes       |
| Account creation              | Yes       |
| Group membership modification | Yes       |
| Sensitive file access         | Yes       |
| Privileged enumeration        | Yes       |

---

### Notes

This scenario represents legitimate administrative activity rather than a privilege escalation attack.

The user `karen` already possessed sudo rights before the actions were performed.

The purpose of the exercise was to validate Linux audit visibility, privileged command monitoring, and dashboard effectiveness within the DarkForest SOC environment.
